      "id": "s03-02",
      "type": "problem",
      "session": "s03",
      "locale": "en",
      "title": "The Problem: TodoWrite",
      "problem": "On multi-step tasks, the model loses track. It repeats work, skips steps, or wanders off. Long conversations make this worse -- the system prompt fades as tool results fill the context. A 10-step refactoring might complete steps 1-3, then the model starts improvising because it forgot steps 4-10.",
      "context": []
    },
    {
      "id": "s03-03",
      "type": "solution",
      "session": "s03",
      "locale": "en",
      "title": "The Solution: TodoManager + nag reminder",
      "solution": "```\r\n+--------+      +-------+      +---------+\r\n|  User  | ---> |  LLM  | ---> | Tools   |\r\n| prompt |      |       |      | + todo  |\r\n+--------+      +---+---+      +----+----+\r\n                    ^                |\r\n                    |   tool_result  |\r\n                    +----------------+\r\n                          |\r\n              +-----------+-----------+\r\n              | TodoManager state     |\r\n              | [ ] task A            |\r\n              | [>] task B  <- doing  |\r\n              | [x] task C            |\r\n              +-----------------------+\r\n                          |\r\n              if rounds_since_todo >= 3:\r\n                inject <reminder> into tool_result\r\n```",
      "principles": [
        "An agent without a plan drifts; list the steps first, then execute",
        "Key design principle",
        "Implementation best practice"
      ]
    },
